The Ghana Cocoa Board said it purchased214 tonnes of cocoa in the 24th week, ended March 19, of the1986/87 main crop season, compared with 456 tonnes the previousweek and 372 tonnes in the 24th week ended March 27 of the1985/86 season.    Cumulative purchases so far this season stand at 217,449tonnes, ahead of the 204,256 tonnes purchased by the 24th weekof last season. REUTER&#3;